HEADWORD: Leghorn
<hw>Leg"horn</hw> <pr>(l⟦ecr⟧g"h⟦ocir⟧rn)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
straw plaiting used for bonnets and hats, made from the straw of a
particular kind of wheat, grown for the purpose in Tuscany, Italy; -- so
called from Leghorn, the place of exportation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

